transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I placed an order in December for a product, a Viagra product, and I want to make sure

Speaker 2: that I am canceled out of subscription.

Speaker 1: I thought it was just a one-time deal, and I'm kind of looking at my account, and it

Speaker 2: looks like it's on a subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I can assist you with that.

Speaker 1: Let me just pull up your account.

Speaker 2: Can I get your name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: James Wilms, W-I-L-L-M-S.

Speaker 2: It's 6-11-1953.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, sir, so you called ScoreBlue, and I'm not seeing any recent orders for you.

Speaker 1: Your last order was in December.

Speaker 2: It was in December.

Speaker 1: Yeah, December 27th.

Speaker 2: I just see one order for $63.85.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's correct.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, good.

Speaker 2: I guess I assumed it was like a recurring charge, but I wanted to be clear, Mr. Wilms,

Speaker 1: that we're not a subscription.

Speaker 2: We're actually a telehealth, so you're not required or locked into any monthly fees.

Speaker 1: You are our VIP customer.

Speaker 2: You can determine the frequency of your orders.

Speaker 1: You can also put a pause on your account for up to 6 months at any time.

Speaker 2: It's just to keep someone a doctor.

Speaker 1: So being a telehealth, when you place the order, we cover the doctor fee, and the doctor

Speaker 2: wrote a prescription with refills.

Speaker 1: Now, as I was mentioning, as our customer, that can vary.

Speaker 2: You know, we do have a lot of customers that like to get their refills every month, and

Speaker 1: we have some that like to get it, you know, twice a year and everything in between.

Speaker 2: We do recommend keeping that prescription available to you with refills so that when

Speaker 1: you call in to place a future order, we can fulfill that order with the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: Well, I'm going to cancel it for right now.

Speaker 1: Okay, because if I cancel it, it will cancel that prescription I just spoke to you about

Speaker 2: and any future refills.

Speaker 1: So if you are planning on placing a future order, I would recommend putting it on a hold.

Speaker 2: Just cancel it, please.

Speaker 1: Okay, you're canceled there.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.
